channel.title: What's your problem with RSPS's?
channel.description:
You see, every new comer to RSPS's have something that always bugs them.
What is the thing that really bugs you when you try to sit down and make a RSPS happen?
To me, the thing that really BUGS the living crap out of me is that I don't know the variables, methods or classes. When I read a todo list I'm like oh hell yea that shit is easy to code. But the thing is, I have no idea where to put those lines of code, or what methods to use.
Also Clients hate the living shit out of me.
